The course gives an overview of different ways of relating to nature in Estonian religions. The environment for religion in prehistoric times was nature, humankind depended on it and their entire religious world was connected with it. During the catholic period a part of the essence of prehistoric religion and spatial memory of holy places were preserved. Some of this was given a Christian context, some retained their original importance and function. Together with the development of nationalism on the 19th centuryObjectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of beliefs and practices connected with nature in the context of religions in Estonia from prehistoric to contemporary times.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student that has passed the course knows different religious discourses connected with nature and 
can use specialized terminology and analyze nature's religious discourses as cultural constructs.
